                <mxCell id="notes" value="• Compose: id = (ip &lt;&lt; 44) | (pid &lt;&lt; 28) | (hlc &amp; 0x0FFFFFFF)&#xa;• Shard: shard(id) = id mod K   (uniform on the IP-prefixed high bits)&#xa;• HLC: thread-safe CAS on packed long; bumps logical counter on tie or skew&#xa;• Bounds NTP skew to ~50 ms; monotonic per process across restarts" style="rounded=0;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;fillColor=#ffffff;strokeColor=#000000;fontSize=11;fontFamily=Courier New;align=left;spacingLeft=10;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="40" y="340" width="800" height="80" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
                <mxCell id="cap" value="&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Figure 5.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;Layout of the 64-bit EventId and the underlying Hybrid Logical Clock. Embedding the HLC in the i&lt;/font&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;d lets the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(63, 63, 63); font-size: 18px; background-color: transparent;&quot;&gt;IdRegistry and Joiner reject expired events without an etcd round-trip, and gives the Dispatcher&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;font style=&quot;font-size: 18px;&quot;&gt;a stable shard key derived from the originating host.&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" style="text;html=1;align=left;fontSize=10;fontStyle=2;" parent="1" vertex="1">
                    <mxGeometry x="40" y="425" width="800" height="40" as="geometry"/>
                </mxCell>
